OL,3,C'Worrying trends' in the number of
OL,4,Cdeaths from alcohol
OL,6,FPHW says there were 683 alcohol-
OL,7,Frelated deaths in Wales in 2023, which
OL,8,Frepresents a 10.5% from the previous
OL,9,Fyear (618) and a substantial rise from
OL,10,Fa decade before (462). Alcohol-
OL,11,Fspecific hospital admissions continue
OL,12,Fto rise with over 12,000 (12,236)
OL,13,Fadmissions involving more than 8,000
OL,14,F(8,147) individuals.
OL,16,FOlder adults aged 50+ made up two
OL,17,Fthirds (67%) of those cases. Highest
OL,18,Fadmission rates were recorded in
OL,19,FMerthyr Tydfil (397 per 100,000
OL,20,Fpeople), more than double the rate in
OL,21,FPowys, which had the lowest admissions.
